    <note>Zhao(1) Xuanfu [27034] According to Xu Xuan, their ancestors were Tianshui Zhao(1), but that the had no fixed residence, but lived where they held office--strong support for my thesis that these people were a professional bureaucratic elite. Since Xuanfu was born in Jiangdu county and was buried in Jiangning, I am making the former address that of his three patrilineal ancestors. He was involved in the campaigns against the kingdom of Min as was his brother-in-law, Cha(1) Wenhui. Xu Xuan, WJ, 15.15a-18a. Not indexed in CBD.</note>
